      <profiles>
        <profile name="Infiltration" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="68c6-6b8f-d6cf-ba16">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">After this unit is Activated in reserves, you may ‘infiltrate’. If you do, roll 2D6+1. Then, Deploy this unit anywhere on the battlefield at least X” away from all enemy units where X is the result of that roll. If you do, this unit cannot March or Fall Back this turn.</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Special Operation" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="52c6-6dc7-e8af-abad">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">After you Activate this unit while it is in reserves or embarked within a transport, you may give it a ‘mission objective’. If you do, choose a unit type (either vehicle, monster or infantry). Until the End step, for each ranged attack this unit makes targeting the chosen unit type, reroll a Wound Roll of 1 for that attack.</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
    </selectionEntry>
